The paper discusses a tool for improving the throughput of electron beam lithography (EBL) systems, which is a topic related to electronic design automation (EDA) and computational engineering (CE). The paper also mentions the use of dynamic programming and clustering techniques, which are commonly used in algorithms and data structures (DS) and data mining (DM). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the stencil planning problem, which is related to numerical analysis (NA). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.ET (EDA and CE), followed by cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, and cs.CE.
